## Provider Configuration — Better Auth

Better Auth is **self-hosted** — there's no external dashboard. All configuration lives in your code and `.env.local`.

### Step 1 — Generate `BETTER_AUTH_SECRET`

This is the symmetric key used to sign session tokens. Anyone with this value can forge sessions — treat it like a database password.

```bash
openssl rand -hex 32
```

Paste the output into `.env.local`:

```env
BETTER_AUTH_SECRET=<paste-here>
```

> **Production:** generate a fresh secret per environment (dev / staging / prod). **Never** reuse the dev secret.

### Step 2 — Set `BETTER_AUTH_URL`

This must **exactly match** the URL your app is served from — no trailing slash, no path.

```env
BETTER_AUTH_URL=http://localhost:3000   # dev
# BETTER_AUTH_URL=https://yourapp.com  # prod
```

A mismatch causes session cookies to be rejected silently. See pitfall #43.

### Step 3 — Database (already set up)

Your Drizzle schema (`src/db/schema.ts`) already includes the four core Better Auth tables:
`user`, `session`, `account`, `verification`.

Run the migration to create them:

```bash
npx drizzle-kit push
```

If you need to add Better Auth plugins later (2FA, organizations, admin), regenerate:

```bash
npx @better-auth/cli generate
npx drizzle-kit push
```

<!-- IF oauth=google -->
### Step 4 — Configure Google OAuth

1. Go to [Google Cloud Console → Credentials](https://console.cloud.google.com/apis/credentials).
2. Create a project (or select an existing one).
3. **OAuth consent screen** → choose **External** → fill the required fields → **Save and continue**. Add your email under **Test users** while in Testing mode.
4. **Credentials** → **Create Credentials** → **OAuth Client ID** → **Web application**.
5. Add **Authorized redirect URIs** — Better Auth uses the **`/api/auth/callback/<provider>`** convention:
   - `http://localhost:3000/api/auth/callback/google` (dev)
   - `https://yourapp.com/api/auth/callback/google` (prod)
6. Click **Create** → copy `Client ID` and `Client Secret` into `.env.local`:

```env
GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=<paste>
GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET=<paste>
```

> ⚠️ Better Auth's callback URL is `/api/auth/callback/google` — **not** Firebase's `/__/auth/handler`. They are different conventions.

Full cross-provider OAuth guide (Google, GitHub, Apple):
→ [`references/07-oauth-social-login.md`](https://github.com/MangalaHQ/shipwithai-plugins/blob/main/plugins/auth/skills/auth-setup/references/07-oauth-social-login.md)
<!-- /IF -->

<!-- IF email=resend -->
### Step 5 — Configure Resend (email delivery)

Better Auth requires you to send verification and password-reset emails yourself. This scaffold uses [Resend](https://resend.com) (free tier: 100 emails/day).

1. Sign up at [resend.com](https://resend.com) → **API Keys** → **Create API Key** → copy.
2. Add to `.env.local`:

```env
RESEND_API_KEY=re_<paste>
EMAIL_FROM=onboarding@resend.dev
```

> ⚠️ **Resend free-tier limitation:** `onboarding@resend.dev` can **only** send to the email address that owns your Resend account. Emails to any other address are silently rejected (403).
>
> To send to any address: verify your own domain at [resend.com/domains](https://resend.com/domains) and switch `EMAIL_FROM=auth@yourdomain.com`.

**Local dev fallback:** if `RESEND_API_KEY` is empty, emails are logged to your terminal — check the dev server output for verification/reset links.

Full Resend setup details:
→ [`references/02-better-auth-guide.md` § Email Provider](https://github.com/MangalaHQ/shipwithai-plugins/blob/main/plugins/auth/skills/auth-setup/references/02-better-auth-guide.md#email-provider--resend)
<!-- /IF -->

<!-- IF email=console -->
### Step 5 — Email delivery (Console-only mode)

You chose **Console-only** email — verification and password-reset URLs are logged to your terminal instead of being sent. Check the dev server output for links.

To switch to a real email provider later, see:
