## Environment Variables

| Variable | Description | Where to get it |
|---|---|---|
| `BETTER_AUTH_SECRET` | 32-byte hex string for signing sessions | Run `openssl rand -hex 32` |
| `BETTER_AUTH_URL` | Exact app URL (no trailing slash) | Manual — `http://localhost:3000` for dev |
| `NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL` | Public URL referenced by the client | Manual — same as `BETTER_AUTH_URL` |
| `DATABASE_URL` | Drizzle DB connection string | Your DB provider (or `file:./dev.db` for SQLite) |
<!-- IF oauth=google -->
| `GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID` | Google OAuth client ID | [Google Cloud Console → Credentials](https://console.cloud.google.com/apis/credentials) |
| `GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET` | Google OAuth client secret | Same as above |
<!-- /IF -->
<!-- IF email=resend -->
| `RESEND_API_KEY` | Resend API key | [resend.com/api-keys](https://resend.com/api-keys) |
| `EMAIL_FROM` | "From" address for outbound mail | `onboarding@resend.dev` (free) or your verified domain |
<!-- /IF -->

> Always keep `.env.local` out of git. The included `.gitignore` handles this.

