## Auth Flow

| Route | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `/register` | Create account (email/password<!-- IF oauth=google --> or Google<!-- /IF -->) → session cookie set automatically → redirect to `/dashboard` |
| `/login` | Sign in (email/password<!-- IF oauth=google --> or Google<!-- /IF -->) |
| `/forgot-password` | Send reset email via `authClient.requestPasswordReset()` |
| `/reset-password` | Completes reset (token from email, Suspense-wrapped) |
| `/dashboard` | Protected — requires `better-auth.session_token` cookie |

Behavior is enforced by:

- `src/middleware.ts` — Edge-Runtime cookie existence check (Better Auth uses `better-auth.session_token`)
- `src/app/(protected)/layout.tsx` — `auth.api.getSession()` cryptographic verification on the server

> Middleware does **not** import the `auth()` wrapper — that's an Auth.js (NextAuth v5) pattern, not Better Auth. See pitfall #43.

